response: "{ \"title\": \"Reverse a string without using built-in functions\", \"description\": \"Given a string s, write a function `reverse(s: str) -> str` that reverses the order of its characters. Do not use any built-in functions for this task.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string of length at least 1\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the reversed string\\n\", \"code\": \"def reverse(s: str) -> str:\\n    s = list(s)\\n    for i in range(len(s) // 2):\\n        s[i], s[-1 - i] = s[-1 - i], s[i]\\n    return ''.join(s)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse('hello') == 'olleh', \\nassert reverse('racecar') == 'racecar'\"] }"
